        <div n="393-38X1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">B</hi>Ehold these Monarch Oaks, that rise,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-2"> With lofty Branches, to the Skies;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-3"> Have huge proportion'd Roots, that grow</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-4"> In equal Longitude below:<gap/><gap/></l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-5"> Two Bards that now in Fashion reign,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-6"> Most aptly this Device explain;</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-7"> If this on Clouds and Stars will venture,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-8"> That will creep downwards to the Centre.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-9"> Or more, to shew the Thing I mean,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-10"> Have you not o'er a Saw-pit seen</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-11"> A skill'd Mechanic, that has stood</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-12"> On a strong Plank of stubborn Wood?</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-13"> Who hir'd a subterraneous Friend,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-14"> To take his Iron by the End;</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-15"> Yet, which excell'd, was never found,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-16"> The Man above, or under, Ground?</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-17"> This Moral is so plain to hit,</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-18"> That, had I been the God of Wit,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-19"> Then in a Saw-pit, and wet Weather,</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-393-38X1-line-20"> Should <hi rend="underline">Young</hi> and <hi rend="underline">Philips</hi> work together.393-38X1   </l></lg></div>
